1 or redevelopment for the purpose of exceeding allowable density under the applicable water
2 supply watershed rules as provided in G.S. 143-214.5(d3). This subsection applies to all local
3 governments regardless of the source of their regulatory authority. Local governments shall
4 include the requirements of this subsection in their stormwater ordinances.
5 …
6 (b8) A local government may offer nonmandatory incentives that waive building, zoning,
7 connection, or other regulations or fees; provide additional tax and financial benefits; or institute
8 other incentives for development or redevelopment that implements additional stormwater
9 control measures beyond those required by this section and rules adopted thereunder.
10 …."
11 SECTION 2.(b) Each local government that implements a stormwater management
12 program shall amend its stormwater ordinance to conform to G.S. 143-214.7(b3), as amended by
13 subsection (a) of this section, within 12 months of the effective date of this section. Any local
14 stormwater ordinance that is inconsistent with G.S. 143-214.7(b3), as amended by subsection (a)
15 of this section, is void and unenforceable on and after that date. A local government may adopt,
16 amend, or repeal ordinance provisions implementing G.S. 143-214.7(b8) at any time after the
17 effective date of this section.
18 SECTION 2.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
19 stormwater rules and stormwater program amendments adopted on or after that date.
20
21 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
22 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
23 law.
